record_data.record_plain_text: PACIFIC NORTHWEST GENERATING COOPERATIVE, INC.Market-Based Rate ScheduleAvailability. Pacific Northwest Generating Cooperative, Inc. (“PNGC”) makes electric energy and capacity available under this Rate Schedule for wholesale sales with which PNGC has contracted.Applicability. This Rate Schedule is applicable to all sales of electric energy or capacity by PNGC not otherwise subject to a particular Rate Schedule of PGNC.Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and PNGC.Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sale shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and PNGC.Effective Date. This Rate Schedule is effective on and after December 23, 2010.Compliance with Regulations of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. PNGC shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning PNGC’s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes PNGC to engage in affiliate sales under this Rate Schedule or otherwise restricts or limits PNGC’s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning PNGC’s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Rate Schedule.Seller Category. PNGC is a Category 2 Seller, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a), in the Northwest Region, and a Category 1 Seller in all other regions.Limitations, Exemptions, Waivers and Blanket Authorizations. PNGC’s market-based rate authority is not subject to any limitations. PNGC has been granted the following waivers and authorizations: (a) waiver of subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission’s regulations, except sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; (b) waiver of Parts 41, 101 and 141; and (c) blanket authorization for issuances of securities or assumptions of liabilities pursuant to Federal Power Act Section 204. Pacific Northwest Generating Cooperative, 78 FERC 61,018 (1997). UNITED STATES OF AMERICABEFORE THEFEDERAL ENERGY REGULATORY COMMISSIONPacific Northwest Generating ) Docket Nos. ER97-504-002 Cooperative ) and OA97-32-000RESPONSE OFDOUGLAS ELECTRIC COOPERATIVE, INC.TO THE COMMISSION’S ORDERISSUED JANUARY 13, 1997 Douglas Electric Cooperative, Inc. (“Douglas Electric”) hereby responds to the Commission’s order issued on January 13, 1997 in these dockets conditionally accepting for filing market-based rates proposed by the Pacific Northwest Generating Cooperative. In the order, the Commission found that Douglas Electric Cooperative, Inc. (Douglas Electric) has limited transmission facilities and required Douglas Electric to make, within 15 days of the date of issuance of the order, the same commitment previously offered by certain other cooperatives respecting compliance with Order 888. See January 13 order at p. 8 (slip. op.). Just as Power Resources Cooperative, Umatilla Electric Cooperative Association, Lost River Rural Electric Cooperative, Inc., and Raft River Rural Electric Cooperative, Inc. committed when PNGC filed its petition in this proceeding (Petition of PNGC at p. 9, filed November 14, 1996), Douglas Electric hereby commits for the period that PNGC’s power marketing tariff is in effect to provide transmission service consistent with Order No. 888, within 60 days of receiving a valid request.
